Steps to install SASS:

1. Navigated to the alx-intermediate-frontend repository:
   cd path/to/alx-intermediate-frontend

2. Created a new directory named 0x03-sass_scss:
   mkdir 0x03-sass_scss
   cd 0x03-sass_scss

3. Installed Node Version Manager (nvm) to manage Node.js versions:
   curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

4. Closed the terminal to apply nvm changes:
   exit

5. Reopened the terminal and installed Node.js version 24.7:
   nvm install 24.7
   nvm use 24.7

6. Verified Node.js installation:
   node -v
   Output: v24.7.0

7. Installed SASS version 1.92.1 globally using npm:
   npm install sass latest version -g

8. Verified SASS installation:
   sass --version
   Output: 1.92.2

9. Created this file (0-installation-script) to document the steps:
   0-installation-script